The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization of a monotone submodular function, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation guarantees, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with budget feasible mechanisms, which is a subfield of economics and market design (cs.EC).
